A fragment of a copper-alloy Late Bronze Age&nbsp;socketed spear (spearhead), c.&nbsp;1200-750&nbsp;BC, comprising the terminal (tip).

The spearhead fragment is broadly sub-triangular and lozenge shaped in cross section. The terminal of the blade is very slightly abraded. The object is broken at the opposing terminal which exposes a circular shaped socket. The break is broadly straight on one side of the socket, and angled upwards on the other.&nbsp;The spearhead has a pronounced midrib which extends&nbsp;longitudinally along the central axis of the object. The edges of the blade are slightly abraded and the spearhead has a well developed smooth,&nbsp;green patina which has a smooth finish and is abraded in places.&nbsp;

Measurements: 50 mm in length, 38 mm in width and 26.38 g in weight
